  "11-14": (
    caption: [Membrane proteins with (cid:2)-barrel structure. Three proteins of the E. coli outer membrane are shown, viewed in the plane of the mem- brane. FepA (PDB ID 1FEP), involved in iron uptake, has 22 membrane- spanning (cid:3) strands. OmpLA (derived from PDB ID 1QD5), a phospholi- pase, is a 12-stranded (cid:3) barrel that exists as a dimer in the membrane. Maltoporin (derived from PDB ID 1MAL), a maltose transporter, is a trimer; each monomer consists of 16 (cid:3) strands. c11BiologicalMembranesAndTransport.indd Page 394 13/09/12 11:42 AM user-F408 c11BiologicalMembranesAndTransport.indd Page 394 13/09/12 11:42 AM user-F408 /Users/user-F408/Desktop /Users/user-F408/Desktop 394],
