    caption: [Kinetics of glucose transport into erythrocytes. (a) The initial rate of glucose entry into an erythrocyte, V0, depends on the initial concentration of glucose on the outside, \[S\]out. (b) Double-reciprocal plot of the data in (a). The kinetics of facilitated diffusion is analogous to the kinetics of an enzyme-catalyzed reaction. Compare these plots with Figure 6–11 and with Figure 1 in Box 6–1. Note that Kt is analogous to Km, the Michaelis constant.],
