  "11-37": (
    caption: [Postulated mechanism of the SERCA pump. The trans- port cycle begins with the protein in the E1 conformation, with the Ca2(cid:2)- binding sites facing the cytosol. Two Ca2(cid:2) ions bind, then ATP binds to the transporter and phosphorylates Asp351, forming E1-P. Phosphory- lation favors the second conformation, E2-P, in which the Ca2(cid:2)-bind- ing sites, now with a reduced affinity for Ca2(cid:2), are accessible on the other side of the membrane (the lumen or extracellular space), and the released Ca2(cid:2) diffuses away. Finally, E2-P is dephosphorylated, returning the protein to the E1 conformation for another round of transport.],
